name "fig:ObliqueIncidence"

\end_inset

Plots of the Transmittance, Reflectance and Fraction of absorbed intensity
 for a wave incident on an interface between air and a glass (
\begin_inset Formula $n=1.57$
\end_inset

).
 We compare the curves obtained with and without a pristine graphene sheet
 deposed on the surface of the glass.
 We considered a negative chemical potential of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu=-0.2\text{eV}$
\end_inset

 and a temperature of 
\begin_inset Formula $T=300K$
\end_inset

.
 The top panels correspond to an air-to-glass interface, while the bottom
 ones show the opposite incidence (see schemes in the corners).
\end_layout

